# Conventional commits

This repo uses **semantic-release** on `main`/`master`. Commit messages must follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
<type>(<optional scope>): <short description>

[optional body]
```

**Types**: `feat` (minor), `fix` (patch), `perf`, `refactor`, `docs`, `style`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`.

**Breaking change**: add `!` after type or `BREAKING CHANGE:` in footer → major version.

Examples:
- `feat(rank): add binary insertion ranking step`
- `fix(auth): handle expired Spotify token`
- `chore: update eslint`

Do not commit unless the user asks. When they do, use messages that will produce the intended release bump.
